==English==

===Etymology===
From the French ''-ette'', (the [[diminutive]] form of the suffix ''-et'')

===Suffix===
'''-ette'''

#Used to form [[noun]]s meaning a smaller form of something.
#:''[[cigarette]]'', ''[[majorette]]''
#Used to form nouns meaning an [[imitation]] or [[substitute]] of something.
#:''[[leatherette]]''
#Used to form nouns of a [[pejorative]] nature, which result in a lowering of status of women.
#:Example:  Calling a female Army Major, a "Majorette", a female lawyer, a "lawyerette", or an unmarried woman a "bachelorette".

